Christian Aid belongs to and supports a wide range of networks and other coalitions in the UK and elsewhere in Europe and globally, many of which are issue-specific and/or ecumenical.&#xd;
&#xd;
With regard to the question about the number of members which Christian Aid has, we need to point out that Christian Aid is a company limited by guarantee owned by its sponsoring churches. We have hundreds of thousands of supporters across the UK and elsewhere, but they are not members. Many, but not all, of them give money, others campaign, others pray or support us in other ways. The question does not allow for that possibility, which is the reason why we put '0' in the relevant box.&#xd;
&#xd;
The countries listed above are those where we have programmes, but we support some regional partners and regional networks which have connections in other countries as well.
